******
[3] Nebraska
Date: Mon 2 Mar 2020
Source: EquiManagement [abridged, edited]
https://equimanagement.com/news/end-of-february-respiratory-disease-update-from-edcc


The attending veterinarian has reported as of [Thu 27 Feb 2020] the voluntary quarantine has been lifted on a premises in Washington County, Nebraska, where one horse was confirmed with respiratory equine herpesvirus and 30 other horses were exposed. No other horses became ill and the affected horse has recovered.

Information for this report was provided by the Equine Disease Communication Center (http://www.equinediseasecc.org).

[byline: Kimberly S Brown]

